.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_TrackObjectGrabAttach
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The Track Object Grab Attach script doesn't attach the object to the controller via a joint, instead it ensures the object tracks the direction of the controller.
.NET Framework 3.5.remarks: This works well for items that are on hinged joints or objects that require to interact naturally with other scene rigidbodies.
.NET Framework 3.5.example: VRTK/Examples/021_Controller_GrabbingObjectsWithJoints demonstrates this grab attach mechanic on the Chest handle and Fire Extinguisher body.

methods.summary: The CreateTrackPoint method sets up the point of grab to track on the grabbed object.
methods.returns: The transform of the created track point.

params.value: The point on the controller where the grab was initiated.
The object that is currently being grabbed.
The object that is currently doing the grabbing.
A reference to whether the created track point is an auto generated custom object.

methods.name: ProcessFixedUpdate()
methods.summary: The ProcessFixedUpdate method is run in every FixedUpdate method on the interactable object. It applies velocity to the object to ensure it is tracking the grabbing object.

methods.name: ProcessUpdate()
methods.summary: The ProcessUpdate method is run in every Update method on the interactable object. It is responsible for checking if the tracked object has exceeded it's detach distance.
